zsh tool that binds various shortcuts to semicolon typed at an empty prompt

currently supports:

    ;g (git)
        follow by various letters to access git functions (e.g. ;gc = git commit)

    ;j (jump)
        use ;j+ to add a jump bind to the current directory
        use ;j* to edit the list of jump binds
        use ;j[bind] to jump to the corresponding directory

    ;c, ;x (compile)
        use ;x to set the "compile" command used in the current directory
        use ;x* to edit this list of compile commands
        use ;c to run the compile command

    ;m (mkdir)
        use ;m to insert "mkdir [current date]_"
